Kenya on Tuesday recorded 280 new cases of Covid 19 from a sample size of 3,105 tested in the last 24 hours. The positivity rate is now at 9.0%. "From the cases, 251 are Kenyans while 29 are foreigners. 150 are males and 130 females," a statement by Health CS read. The youngest is a one-year-old baby while the oldest is 90-years-old. Total confirmed positive cases are now 327,425 and cumulative tests so far conducted are 3,706,945. "On Tuesday, 122 patients have recovered from the disease; 117 are from the Home-Based and Isolation Care Program while five are from various health facilities countrywide," CS Kagwe said. The number pushes the total recoveries to 319,791 of whom 266,740 are from the Home-Based Care and Isolation program, while 53,051 are from various health facilities countrywide. No patient has succumbed to the disease therefore the cumulative fatalities remain at 5,651. There are 49 patients currently admitted to the health facilities, while 1,934 are under the Home-Based Isolation and Care program. Three patients are in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) and are on supplemental oxygen. The number of patients in the General Wards is four. No patient is in the High Dependency Unit (HDU). In terms of County distribution; Nairobi 178, Kiambu 36, Bungoma 25, Nakuru 15, Murangâ€™a has eight cases, Siaya recorded seven cases, and Kajiado and Nyandarua have four cases each while Kericho, Nyeri and Kilifi have one case each.